Name: CVE-2005-0708
Description: The sendfile system call in FreeBSD 4.8 through 4.11 and 5 through 5.4 can transfer portions of kernel memory if a file is truncated while it is being sent, which could allow remote attackers to obtain sensitive information.
References: FREEBSD:FreeBSD-SA-05:02   |   URL:https://www.freebsd.org/security/advisories/FreeBSD-SA-05:02.sendfile.asc

Name: CVE-2005-0712
Description: Mac OS X before 10.3.8 users world-writable permissions for certain directories, which may allow local users to gain privileges, possibly via the receipt cache or ColorSync profiles.
References: APPLE:APPLE-SA-2005-03-21   |   URL:http://lists.apple.com/archives/security-announce/2005/Mar/msg00000.html

Name: CVE-2005-0713
Description: The Bluetooth Setup Assistant for Mac OS X before 10.3.8 can be launched without a keyboard or Bluetooth device, which allows local users to bypass access restrictions and gain privileges.
References: APPLE:APPLE-SA-2005-03-21   |   URL:http://lists.apple.com/archives/security-announce/2005/Mar/msg00000.html
